      "The learner must identify that large-scale generation is required because micro-generation (like domestic PV) is too small-scale to meet the bulk power demands of an entire city.",
      "The learner must correctly identify 400 kV (or 275 kV / 132 kV) as a standard UK transmission voltage.",
      "The learner must explain that stepping up to high voltage reduces the current, which minimizes I²R losses (energy wasted as heat) over the long distance between the wind farm and the city."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about the difference in power output between a wind farm and a house roof, and remember how we keep the cables from getting hot over long distances."
  }
}
